                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d259">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A16/70: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-10-02T20:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 2, 1928—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 2—1:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>92. Next session of private manufacture conference called for December 5th. If I
                    am to represent Department again it would be of great help in preparing myself
                    to receive as soon as possible detailed comment from the Department on stand
                    taken by delegation during the last session (see despatch No. 584, September
                    10).</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
